A Great Buy
In Brief: <br />This netbook provides stellar battery life, admirable performance, and is priced very competitively.<br /><br />Me as a user:<br />I'm a Technology & Management consultant, who is now attending grad school for a PhD. My classes are three-hours long a piece and my 17" laptop was going to be too heavy and cumbersome to lug around campus, not to mention having to plug in for every class. <br /><br />I was looking for netbook primarily to take notes and do some light web-work (DreamWeaver and Expression Web). <br /><br />Keyboard & Touchpad:<br />I have large hands so my biggest concern with a netbook was being able to type quickly and comfortably. The keyboard, despite smaller but more spaced out keys (compared to say the HP Minis), was easy to use and I was able to type with no adjustment to my usual habits.  The keys also have a nice tactile feel, unlike the more floating feeling on, again, the HP Mini.<br /><br />As is a complaint of big reviews like those on CNET, the rocker-bar mouse-buttons is a little stiff, but not the end of the world - I think it may ease up after some use.<br /><br />Performance:<br />The initial startup, which involved Windows 7 initializing the installation, took around 10-15-minutes - so don't expect to turn it on and hit the desktop right away.<br /><br />From power-on to the Windows desktop, takes about 25-30 seconds.  <br /><br />Overall responsiveness from the desktop and launching applications was quick.  After installing Office 2007 Pro, Word took about 6-seconds to load the first time, and was about 2-3 seconds to load after that. Chrome is very quick to load; browsing and overall network performance is very good.<br /><br />Media:<br />Steaming video, like Hulu, is a big test for a lot of netbooks - this model can play full screen videos with only an occasional stutter or slow-down - I tested an episode of The Daily Show. Local video files (played off a USB flash drive) played without issue. <br /><br />The speaker volume is loud enough to hear in an open room with some background noise, but not in a crowded hall.<br /><br />Other Thoughts:<br />I debated a lot between this model and the HP Mini 311 with nVidia ION for better performance at the cost of battery life. I can say that so far I feel that I made the right choice, since the HP Mini would have cost around 100.00 more for the configuration with matching N-Wifi, BlueTooth, and Windows 7 - which comes on this netbook.<br /><br />I highly recommend the ASUS Eee PC 1005PE.
      
