The PERFECT netbook, returned the Toshiba NB305 and bought this instead ... NO REGRETS
I ordered the Toshiba NB305 and returned it to get this instead. I have NO REGRETS and am VERY SATISFIED with my purchase.<br /><br />PROS:<br />- Battery life is amazing. Even on the highest settings, I can get around 9 hours. Unmatched.<br />- Keyboard. I returned the Toshiba NB305 due to its weird keyboard. This has one of the BEST keyboards I've typed on. It's chiclet style and perfect for touch typists because the keys are in the right place unlike the Toshiba. The keys are obviously a bit smaller. They feel good, and they're responsive. This is the MAIN reason I decided to keep this netbook.<br />- Sound. Netbooks should not be used without earphones but if you must use the speakers, these are LOUD. The Toshiba NB305 had almost no sound so this is a huge improvement.<br />- Price. This is $40 cheaper than the Toshiba NB305.<br />- Weight. This is lighter than the Toshiba NB305.<br /><br />CONS:<br />- Screen is dimmer than the Toshiba NB305 but after a while I didn't notice. Plus, I think it saves more battery life and it is STILL bright.<br />- TOUCHPAD BUTTON!! Instead of two designated touchpad buttons, there's this touchpad bar thing and it's VERY stiff. I do not like using it and it really tires my fingers out. I wish ASUS would make two designated touchpad buttons.<br />- FINGERPRINT MAGNET. One of the things I liked about the Toshiba NB305 was its impeccable looks. This ASUS will not draw any looks because the blue and black are really plain but I can't deny its functionality. I wish ASUS would add more colors to its line.
      
