Just what I wanted!! Wonderful little computer!
I came into the market with a goal of finding a netbook that was very portable had great battery life, and was comfortable for extended periods of time. Mainly I wanted one I could use for web-browsing and screenwriting. This little guy lived up to all my expectations.<br /><br />I was very concerned about a few things at first:<br />-The glossy screen<br />-The keyboard/mouse<br />-Windows 7 starter<br /><br />The screen actually is great. I was super worried about glare but it hasn't been a problem, it's bright, clear and even though its smaller then laptops its still a great size. You can zoom in very easily, and I've found the best way to make use of the available screen space is to set the Taskbar to auto-hide and then use Google Chrome as a browser, because it takes up even less space than FireFox.<br /><br />The keyboard's fantastic, expecially the chicklet style layout of the keys, feels great and not cluttered. The mouse is good, once you get used to the surface its fine and I love the multi-touch functions so that you can scroll, zoom, and flip pages with it. The click bar isnt the best, but its not bad either, i wish it was slightly bigger, but oh well. I've typed on it for long periods of time and it feels good, and doesnt hurt my hands.<br /><br />Windows 7 has been superb! I love the look of it, the feel, its very responsive and much more fun to work in than XP. I was very worried because i know Starter Edition doesn't allow you to change your desktop background, well don't worry! Asus includes a wonderful program that takes care of a few things for you, and this includes allowing you to change your wallpaper, you can even make it into a slideshow so it will shuffle through multiple backgrounds at whatever interval you set it to shuffle at. The new features are nice though it doesn't have the seethrough aspect that premium does, nor does it show thumbnail previews on the taskbar, but for what im using the netbook for, it functions just great.<br /><br />Other notable things I love are:<br />- BATTERY!!!<br />- Speakers<br />- Weight<br /><br />The battery is amaaaaazing. Im so glad i got the long lasting one. I've never tried testing out how long it goes for, but its such a thrill to have it sitting on my lap and still know theres 6 hours left on it when it hasnt been charged all day. I can close the lid and leave it unplugged for days only to pick it up and still have hours and hours left on it :)<br />Not once have I had to worry about running out of juice while im on the go.<br /><br />I was worried the speakers might not be powerful enough but I haven't had a problem with them at all.<br /><br />And finally the size and weight it perfect, i was reallllly debating for a while about going with a 10,11, or 12 inch, and I'm glad i went with the 10, anything bigger is bordering on laptop territory and this size just feels right, its not too thick or heavy, it feels light and compact and easy to just grab and go which is exactly what you should be looking for a in a netbook. Overall I'm super happy with my choice!
      
