I Love This Netbook!
I had initial reservations about going from a full sized, full featured laptop to a net book.  Since I've retired my computer needs have changed and I thought a net book could be a good fit for me now.  I did much research and online shopping.  My main requirement was battery life.  I wanted something I could use unplugged for an entire day when necessary. I have been using laptops since they came out and have always been disappointed by having to plug them in after a couple of hours.<br />After the initial charge the first day, I used the computer as I normally would and 15 hours later I plugged it in so I could go to bed.  It was still at 10% power!  It has performed likewise everyday for over a month, I unplug it in the morning and plug it in at bedtime.  It only takes about three hours to charge. <br /> <br />The computer is very well built and speaks quality in every way. The monitor is clear and bright.  The keyboard is stated to be 92% regular size, but fits my hands better than my last laptop and I find it easier to use. The wi-fi is easy and fast to set up and picks up any network close by with no trouble. The 250G hard drive is larger than any I've had on previous laptops.<br /><br />I cannot think of anything negative to say at this point. It's all I want or need in a laptop at this time. After six laptops I've finally got one that's truly portable and can travel with me.  I couldn't be happier. I LOVE It!<br />p.s. Amazon had the very best price on the very latest model.
      
