Great Netbook, even better battery life!
This little netbook is great. Its like it's the perfect size! <br /><br />The battery life is amazing, even on the super performance mode. You can probably get 6 hours of video play on this thing!<br /><br />The keyboard is almost full size, but still takes a little bit of getting used to. The middle of the keyboard has kind of a pingy/cheap sound/feel to it, but overall its fine.<br /><br />The webcam is ok. Its only 0.3 megapixel so its a little grainy, but for routine Skype use it works fine. <br /><br />I like the charger and cord. They come with little velcro straps and they are long yet compact. The charger connects to the netbook on the side near the back. The connector is very small and does not stick out much to minimize being banged and damaged. <br /><br />The glossy surface is not a big deal to me. People complain about it being a fingerprint magnet. Who cares? Just have a cloth nearby and wipe it off once in a while! Again, not a biggie IMHO.<br /><br />The trackpad works fine. My other laptop has a scroll up/down feature which is really nice. This netbook does not have that feature fyi... The trackpad works by tapping or with the use of the toggle button. What you'll find with the trackpad button is that it is quite stiff, which is another common complaint on these reviews. <br /><br />Windows 7 starter is kind of crappy. You can't play movies on it unless you download VLC player, and I don't like VLC player. you can't change the desktop background or use the nice aero feature on Win 7 either. It feels like a cheap knock off copy of the real thing. When you find out you can't do this and you can't do that, you feel kind of cheated. I upgraded to Win 7 Home Premium and I'm very happy with it. <br /><br />Overall this is a great product especially if you want it for school or you travel a lot. The battery life is great and was definitely the selling feature for me. I would recommend getting the $50 CD/DVD player/burner along with it so you can watch DVD's and install hard copy programs.
      
