ASUS Seashell just right...
I purchased the ASUS Eee PC Seashell 1005PE-PU17-BK for my Wife.  She wanted a light weight small unit that she could do email and Facebook on basically. I'm the computer geek, so I was looking for a nice viewing screen, good feel on the keyboard, good price and features, but most of all GREAT battery life.  This unit had just hit the streets with a new processor that claimed up to 14 hours of battery life. Overall it fulfilled both our needs and wants.  And because it is a netbook, it fits inside most of my wife's purses. The keyboard has a decent feel if you are a touch typist and seems a bit larger than some netbook keyboards.  The trackpad is the same black color and therefore blends in with the surrounding area, but is easy to detect because it is covered with very tiny "bumps". ASUS says that its' quick startup and long battery life is also because it uses Windows 7 Starter. The battery life is pretty right on when doing email and basic surfing the internet.  Of course, if you are doing video or light weight gaming, it will fall off but will still surprise you.  Remember it does not have a built-in CD or DVD drive. I purchased the ASUS external DVD Writer <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001U02JZ8">ASUS USB 2.0 8x DVD Writer External Optical Drive SDRW-08D1S-U (Black)</a>. It works great...and does not have a power plug or "brick". Its' power comes straight from this netbook. It comes with a two headed USB plug that connects directly to the side-by-side USB ports on the ASUS Seashell. The two connections allow it enough power to function properly. One other thing to know is that this unit is black, GLOSS BLACK! NICE! But that means that you will see EVERY finger print and smudge. ASUS does include a small microfiber towel and it does get plenty of use.
      
