Best I've read this year
I have been anxiously awaiting the sequel and was not disappointed. This is a wonderfully written novel that kept me on my toes from start to finish. Although I suggest reading the first before this one, it does stand alone. I think some of the reasons for relationships might get lost without reading  the book. You might wonder why loyalties fall where they do.<br /><br />I haven't read a better book in quite  a long time. There is a tremendous amount of sexuality, some disturbing used to paint a vivid picture of the main character and of the theme of the novel. There are violent parts but none are graphically described. If you have see a thrilling movie recently, this shouldn't bother you. As in the first one, the author takes his time in the beginning developing a character. In this case, the main character is very unique and quite disturbed. Still, I loved her.<br /><br />I won't give away even one plot twist, there are several other reviewers who have shared that. I will say that the ending fit  story perfectly, I laughed in admiration of the author's perfect lines. He is an excellent writer. I am not sure I can wait for the final one to be translated. Wonder if Amazon has anything on how to learn Swedish. This writing might just make me do it.
      
