Much improved
I bought this to replace a 360 I bought shortly after they launched -- back when the only way to get one was on eBay.  While that one was perfectly fine it did have a few annoying drawbacks.  Mainly the noise and the heat.  Frankly, it was like having a space heater in the room as it would quickly get very hot in there.<br /><br />Well, I am glad to say this new Elite (manufactured in Aug 09) is almost totally silent and while slightly warm (although cooler than all my other electronics including my cable box), it no longer heats up like my other one did.  Throw in the 120GB hard drive (which now is really a must with all the downloadable games and content) and you have a great deal.<br /><br />In fact, one of the things that I love most and use my Xbox probably more than anything is the Netflix streaming.  Once you start using that, it's hard to imagine not having it.  While yes, not every DVD is available and the selection has primarily older releases, there is still more than enough to satisfy.  Who needs cable?<br /><br />The two games bundled with this are not great but their not bad.  They come boxed together in one clamshell -- so no cheap little sleeve like most bundles on other products.<br /><br />Also, the cables that come with this are different as I see with some other Elite consoles so be sure to check!<br /><br />I don't own a PS3 so I can't really make comparisons but I do own a Wii and never play it compared to my 360 (and the avatars on 360 make the Wii ones look pathetic).  There are tons of games available both by disc and download so you should be able to find something no matter what your taste.  <br /><br />I agree with the previous reviewer about this guy making all sorts of negative reviews on every xbox product that he doesn't even own most likely.  Obviously a PS3 shill.  While Xbox is not perfect -- yes in the past there was a high rate of failure (that should go way down now with the new versions) his reviews are completely off-base.  And since 360 game titles outsell PS3 ones 3-1, it's not hard to see where developers will put their budgets.  I will probably get a PS3 but really just as a Blu-Ray player when I feel like it down the road.<br /><br />So as a first time buyer or someone looking to replace their old one -- highly recommended!
      
