Get this bundle...
If you are looking to buy an Xbox 306.. do yourself a favor and buy this bundle. Not only does it come with two games (which are not system sellers but a good addition) it also comes with 120 GB hard drive and a HDMI slot. It also comes with a wireless controller and a wired headset. These are all great additions to the system. Considering that Amazon is now bundling a $50 gift card with every purchase, this item is a steal in my opinion. If you are planning to buy an Xbox, spend the additional $100 and buy this system. You will not regret it.<br /><br />Now, let me get to the rants. No WIRELESS!! Seriously Microsoft, this is not 2006. You cannot ask people to buy a $70 wireless adapter in 2010 when both Wii and PS3 have it built in to their systems. <br /><br />No HD cables. I understand most people still have SDTVs. The included cables can only output 480p. Most games on Xbox don't even support this mode anymore. Sure, the graphics are fine but you will end up with having to deal with blurry text in most games if you are playing with the standard cables shipped with Xbox. I suggest you get the HD cables from Microsoft for another $25 or so. <br /><br />Paying for Xbox live gold. The Wii online service and PS3 online service are both free. However, Xbox live is about $40 per year (usually $50). You will get a month of Xbox live trial gold with a purchase of this system. You will need it to stream Netflix movies, access Facebook, Twitter and Last.fm. The silver account is free but it is as good as not having an online service at all. (My suggestion is to snag it on ebay for $30 or less). There is also no browser like Wii or PS3.<br /><br />Other than the three things mentioned above, Xbox is a great system to play games. It already has a lot of great games to play. Most of them are available as Platinum Hits for a $20-$30 price range (about half as much as they initially sold for). There are also great new games like Dragon Age, Mass effect, Final Fantasy. Many more new games are coming this year including Microsoft's motion controller Project Natal. You will have ton of games to play. I will not compare it to PS3 as I do not own one. Comparing it to Wii (which I do own) will not do justice for either of them. They are both catered to different kinds of gamers.
      
