Great deal
I would like to start off by saying that I have owned a 360 from launch.  Overall this is a great deal.<br /><br />Comes with <br />- 2 Black wireless controls<br />- 250gb Hard drive<br />- Black mic<br />- special edition console <br />- power brick<br />- Regular red/white/yellow audio video cables (NO R/G/B)<br />- ethernet cable<br />- Modern Warfare 2 game<br /><br />***DOES NOT COME WITH<br /><br />HDMI cable - not a big deal since you can grab one online for less than $8 with shipping. I was a little surprised seeing that the last 2 elites I bought had the cable included.<br /><br />HDMI AV Cable<br /><br /><br /><br />Overall as a package it is a pretty good deal. You get a HUGE 250 gig hard drive, I believe it ends up being around 228gb of free space when you turn on your system. You get 2 controls instead of the usual 1, which is great if you have buddies or family to play with (don't hog all the fun!). On top of that you get Modern Warfare 2 which is a great game. I love the console as a whole it runs almost silent and very cool. It also looks awesome.<br /><br /><br />There is one thing i disliked about the deal though. That is it doesn't come with any HD video cables out of the box. Then it doesn't have the cable for HD audio (optical) in the box either. This wasn't a problem for me because I still had a pair of both these cables from another elite system I bought in the past. However, if i was a first time buyer  might have been a little ticked that I basically have to buy a $50 cable package (Microsoft sells both their brand hdmi cable and the audio cable you would need in a package together for $50 <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000UODATY">Xbox 360 HDMI AV Cable</a> ). <br /><br /><br />Overall I am VERY pleased with my purchase and plan to be for a long time to come.<br /><br /><br />Just a side note about xbox live I'm not sure that a lot of people know. When you buy a new system you get to create a gamer tag, most people assume you have to pay whatever the fee is to try xbox live out and play online. However when you create the gamer tag sign up for the silver membership. At the end of the process it will give you the option to upgrade to gold for 1 month for free. You can do this around 3 times i believe per system. Hope this helps a few people out that want to try out xbl for free.<br /><br />You wont regret buying this!<br />
      
