Better for the average player than Modern Warfare 1
Love this game.  I have played all of the COD series since the beginning and hands down this is the best.  The single player is great, especially on veteran.  However, multiplayer is why you buy COD and here are my thoughts on that:<br /><br />Pros<br />-Great framerate and graphics combined<br />-Great variety of weapons<br />-Addicting leveling and achievement<br />-Many game modes<br />-New maps will be coming out regularily<br />-All your friends are playing it<br />-Spec Ops is great with a buddy<br /><br />Cons<br />-Still some cheating/glitching, the javelin glitch ruined the game for two weeks<br />-Pretty much no teamwork unless you play with friends or older players<br />-Takes away from your time with all the other great games that came out over the last few months<br /><br /><br />I would offer the following hints to the newer players or anyone who doesn't have the twitch reflexes of a 14 year old who plays for 8 hours a day.<br /><br />-Deathmatch and Team Deathmatch have simple rules but can also be frustrating to the non-elites who wonder why they spawn and die within seconds.  Try Domination or sabotoge where you don't always have to focus on "spray and pray."<br /><br />-Don't copy someone's loadout just because they are getting the most kills.  For example, my kill/death ratio is crappy, about .86.  However, my win/loss ration on Domination is much higher than 50/50 because I play to my strengths and think about teamwork first.  Because I am not able to beat most people gun to gun, I use the explosives perk and set mines around a captured flag and defend.  80% of players in this game will cap a flag and move on to the next one.  That works for some but not a person like me who sometimes even misses his mouth when eating.  I also equip the grenade launcher attachment which ensures I can defend and pop out and kill someone with one general vacinity shot instead of 10 shots to the body.<br /><br />-Using the defend strategy you can get killstreaks easier and supply drops will occasionally have some great items like an AC-130.  I was lucky to get a UAV in the original Modern Warfare.<br /><br />In summary, great game-buy now.<br />
      
