From the 360 to PS3
I've had a 360 for over 2 years and am currently on on my 3rd. The first two had to be replaced, for free, after the RRoD. The DVD player on my latest 360 died and I didn't want to pay to have it repaired so I did it myself. And yes, I modded it. It only cost $50 to replace the DVD player and everything was just dandy. Borderlands came out and I wanted to play the game online with some work friends, so I coughed up the money for XBox live. Almost a week to the day of buying XBL my console got banned from XBL for being modded. Of course we were offered no refund for XBL. Needless to say I was a bit ticked off. I wouldn't have had to mod my 360 if they'd just build a solid device, but I was 0 for 3 on 360 consoles and just didn't want to spend the time and money shipping the thing out for repairs for the third time in less than 3 years. So I retired the 360 to the confines of storage and bought a PS3.<br /><br />I got the Slim and so far so good. The console is much quieter than the 360 and the foot print is a lot smaller than the 360. I traded in all my 360 games and stocked up on my staples, Bioshock, Assians Creed, Dragon Age etc. <br /><br />For me personally I find the failure rate of the 360s to be unacceptable. Most of the people I work with have both a 360 and PS3 and most of them are on their second or third 360, it's just a piece of junk in my opinion. So moving up to a PS3 buys me a bit more security in the fact that this device will perform and not die every year as the 360s do.
      
