Masterpiece-Definitely, Perfection-let's see...
The first GOW game I played was gow2, after I finished I declared it the best game ever. I had some personal problems with it but it was the best game for me. How can it ever be topped? By creating gow3!God of War III is a masterpiece, every element of it was done with the greatest care and precision. Everything about it is stunning and exemplary... I just love this game. Here's why. <br /><br />Story: GOW 3 starts off where GOW 2 finished. Enough about what you've seen in other reviews, what you might not expect is getting a deeper look into the character of Kratos. We know about the past and the motivations of Kratos, in this game we go deeper into his psyche and explore his state of mind as he rages war against Zeus and the rest of the olympians. We see more rage and brutality (i never thought that was possible) and a we get a look at a paternal side of Kratos further in the story. Furthermore this story is tightly-knit. Everything is explained in a coherent manner. Nothing is contrived, gratuitous or left out. It's nice to see that a well-developed story is emphasized in a game like this. It's a simple a revenge story that would be complete without the emphasis, but it just adds to the greatness of this game. <br /><br />Characters: Kratos is bad-ass as ever and I explained what he's like earlier, the other characters and their voice actors deliver top-notch performances. (Except for Aphrodite) I don't know what else to say about them. I'm speechless. I get rage whenever I'm supposed to feel rage against them (especially Zeus) and I'm sympathetic and intrigued when sympathetic characters appear. A++. <br /><br />Graphics: Absolutely jaw dropping. it's hard to tell the difference between a pre-rendered cutscene and gameplay footage. There is no screen tearing,no slow-down anywhere. The level of detail surpasses great PS3 exclusives like Uncharted 2 and MGS4. During battle, when it get more intense, you can actually see Kratos' muscles tense up as he delivers damage. Blood sticks to him and any other enemy when is spews all of the place. (This happens often.) The scale of this game is the crowning achievement of this game. The fighting on Gaia is one of the most heart-pounding fights I've ever had. It looks amazing, it feels amazing, you cannot miss that experience. <br /><br />Gameplay: If it aint broke, don't fix it... Build upon it! That's the philosophy with this game. They raised the level of perfection in this game. It's more fluid, intuitive, and just a hell of alot of fun just killing waves of enemies. Buy the game, see how fun it is, it's worth more than $60.  <br /><br />Replayability: That's not a real word but it should be. You can play this game over and over again with the items and skins you've unlocked and you'll have a different experience everytime. The challenges outside the game are quite hard though, a few are irritating and there is one that is just pointless but it does not diminish the game's greatness.<br /><br />All in all, BUY THIS GAME NOW!! DO NOT MISS OUT ON ONE OF THE GREATEST GAMES OF ALL TIME. That's right I said it, ALL TIME! Past, present, future, this game surpasses all! <br /><br />Note:For me there is just one negative. I'm being honest about this game so I have to put up a negative comment when it comes up. Some of the olympians are TOO easy to kill. In the first game, Ares was ridiculously hard to kill. In the second one, you don't kill any olympians (except the sisters of fate) mostly the heroes, and they had satisfying battles (and deaths. especially theseus). In this game, the olympians, (even though they're supposed to be stronger) are killed very easily. I won't give up any spoilers but 2 die by a broken neck and one dies by losing a NON-VITAL  organ. What the hell? That's too easy. Great game anyway. It's fun to watch them die.
      
