Is going to soon be the system that is remembered in 7th generation...
This is the system of tomorrow. I had serious doubts about the PS3 when it first came out, and I believe Sony rushed it. The game developers weren't ready and the technology was too expensive for the mass market because of including Blu-Ray. If it wasn't for the success of the PS2 and the fact that Sony is a household name, not to mention a rich company, kept sales of the PS3 afloat when it had no great games and was too expensive. Now the price has dropped and the game selection is growing at such a rapid rate that it's killer games will soon outpace those of the XBox 360. The XBox's zenith ended after the Halo 3, Bioshock, and Mass Effect concentrated releases. Now all the XBox has left is Fable 2, while the PS3 is just getting started. In my mind the XBox 360 is not a next generation console, it was a transion console of sorts, just polishing old technology. If there is a new XBox this Winter or Fall, this will most likely be what I consider Microsoft's next generation console. The PS3 is the console with a future, and it is becoming clearer with every passing month. I'm not going to get into the Wii I personally believe it's gimmicky and is just a trend like the Prius. Blu-Ray is also becoming more of a blessing and less of a curse for the PS3, as it's allowing the PS3 exclusive games to include more data than ever imagined just a few years ago. Up to 50 gigabytes and growing! Hypothetically 200 gigabytes. 200! That's 25 times more than the XBox's and Wii's dual layer DVD's! Although the PS3 started off slow, it will soon surpass the XBox 360 and/or it's successor with time. The Wii will, if we are all lucky, will crash in sales like the gimmick it is.<br /><br />PROS:<br />-40 GB HDD (If you ask me, this is plenty, plus you can switch it out for a bigger one)<br />-Blu-Ray (Already a committed user, I love it, it blows DVD away)<br />-No loud fan (The XBox 360 has a very noisy fan)<br />-Built in power brick (XBox 360 has a massive one that takes up precious room)<br />-Sleek design (Nice curves, touch sensitive buttons, glossy black, chrome trim. It looks awesome)<br />-Discs don't scratch (I've had a few XBox 360 games be ruined by scratches, the same with DVD's, but Blu-Ray discs have a super-hard coating that prevents them from being scratched. Love it.)<br />-Slew of upcoming great games (Gran Turismo [looks awesome, even though it's just a prologue], Metal Gear Solid, MLB '08: The Show, God of War 2, Killzone 2, etc.)<br />-Most games are cross-system now (Most XBox games you should be able to play on PS3 as well)<br />-Motion-sensing controllers (Also the new Dualshock 3's with rumble)<br />-Web-Browser (Can surf the web)<br />-Can store a lot of photos and music (I don't think the XBox 360 can even store photos)<br /><br />CONS:<br />-Playstation Network isn't that good (XBox live is better at the moment, Sony lacks online experience, XBox started it for consoles)<br />-Expensive games vs. Wii (XBox prices are the same)<br />-That's basically it!
      
