New Colors Options Amazing
I purchased both the Red color and the Blue Color (at the time of this writing only the blue one has arrived).<br /><br />I must say that the Metallic Blue Dual Shock 3 looks more impressive in person than the image seems to convey.  The image doesnt convey the fact that it is metallic blue.  Metallic blue in this case means that the actually controlloer looks almost nearly like a dark shade of blue but has the "subtle sparks" in it that makes it shimmer and shine when one rotates it around in the lighting.<br /><br />Performance wise it is the same that we expect with all of our DualShock 3's.  Perfect feel for comfort, strong vibrant vibration, and great sixaxis motion control translation (on games that support them). <br /><br />The only other minor thing is that the "DualShock 3" logo and the "Sixaxis" logo are in a brighter blue on that front end of the DualShock 3.  I dont think it adds or distracts from the aesthetics since it is in an odd position on the DualShock 3 for this Metallic Blue color.<br /><br />EDIT:  Deep Red Color arrived today and it looks exactly like the picture.  Saying deep red is quite a stretch for it is a brilliant red but doesnt look quite luminous. <br /><br /><br />These are a worthwhile purchase if you want to add a DualShock 3 color other than Black to your collection.
      
