Uncharted 2 the Masterpiece.
When it comes to gaming, there are games that can be horrible, mediocre, good or even great, but then there are the true classics that rarely comes along and Uncharted 2: Among Thieves is one of them. The first Uncharted had set a very good bar to overcome and the sequel definitely surpasses it with leaps and bounds. Let me first say that whoever thinks this game is over-hyped or over-rated are clearly 1. XBox 360 Fanboys, and 2. Gamers with no clue on what a classic is. The evidence is there: 25 Perfect Gaming Magazine Editorial Scores, over 30 Game of the Year Awards, and has a Top 10 Ranking All-Time on [...]. Now with the haters out of the way Uncharted 2: Among Thieves brings Nathan Drake back for a second epic adventure. This is a 3rd Person Action-Adventure/Platformer filled with gunfights, beautiful cutscenes, and a fantastic story. For a brief explanation of the story, without giving much away, Nathan Drake goes on a journey to discover the truth of Marco Polo's lost fleet and Shambhala's legendary Himalayan valley. In my review I'll cover and rate the game on Presentation, Graphics, Sound, Gameplay, and Replayability.<br /><br />Presentation 10/10: Uncharted 2: Among Thieves has a fantastic story. Its deeply filled with plot twist, deception, action, and suspense. The cutscenes are all spectacular and will leave you in awe. <br /><br />Graphics 10/10: This is thee best game out now in terms of graphics. You will be stunned by the beauty of its design, the characters and levels are all in superb detail. If you want a game that takes full advantage of your PS3 look no further. <br /><br />Sound 10/10: The voice acting is amazing. The weapon effects and explosions are all done with great detail and the game's soundtrack is one of the best ever.<br /><br />Gameplay 10/10: This game is action-packed. The gunplay is incredible, the new stealth system works very well, and the puzzles are actually fun. Lastly the online multiplayer/Co-op is spectacular.<br /><br />Replayability 10/10: The single player campaign can take you 10-15 hours easily. The story and gameplay are both so great multiple playthroughs are highly likely. Then the online itself will make you addicted with experience points and a level system from 1-60. <br /><br />My Overall Experience: This game is a classic hands down. Is this game worth your $60? Yes. It has the perfect combination of visuals, gameplay, and replayability not many other games have. This is a must have for all PS3 owners.
      
