This review is not subsequent to "getting on the bandwagon" with other reviewers...but it wouldn't hurt.<br /><br />Instantly, you are immersed into edge-of-the-seat death-defying action!  Uncharted 2 catches you off guard on a regular basis, leaving little to no room for letting your guard down.<br /><br />The graphics are plush with great contrast ratio bringing out each color and making it easier to identify objects.<br /><br />Gameply acrobatics are unothidox (a good thing) as you hurlde over rooftop beams (don't slip), leap across large gaps that would lead to your untimely death should you fail the jump and creative interactive gaming sequences (ie. defusing alarm systems).<br /><br />This game is unlike any other game because it MAKES you utilize your surroundings (also a good thing).  Causing you to climb poles, leap across ledges while hanging off them, shimmy, and navigate rooftops & high areas.<br /><br />The story line is somewhat typical, with the proverbial double-cross, but it adds to the drama and is still great and you won't regret the purchase if you are into this type of genre.<br /><br />
      
