Uncharted 2 is Among the Best
The long awaited and eagerly anticipated sequel to the most exciting cinematic game experience I've had since the original 'Uncharted: Drake's Fortune' and 'Metal Gear Solid 4' is finally here. <br /><br />Drenched with colorful, lush, and bright graphic and environment with some intensely dark atmosphere, this is the liveliest and most awe-inspiringly beautiful game this year and it's the feat few games have ever come close to in the history of video game.  Graphics definitely improved slightly from already top-notch original.  Animation is fluid, natural, and life-like, captured by now-common Hollywood filmmaking motion-capture technology to create CGI. In fact, everything in this game is superbly on par with the best of top-notch Hollywood summer blockbuster. This game is better than anything I've seen during this year's (2009) dreadful summer movie line-ups. Griping pulpy action-adventure storyline in remeniscent of 'Indiana Jones' series, exciting orchestra and atmospheric scores using lots of drums and flutes, intense 3rd-person action, platform and puzzle gameplay mechanics and seamlessly integrated cutscenes peppered with many filmmaking techniques and signature camera movements are nothing short of brilliant. It borrows the best elements from various games and movies, thoroughly digests, and in turn creates something so familiar yet different.  U2 oozes with quality in every second it's on your screen.<br /><br />Despite the wave after wave of baddies with assortments of guns and more guns, this is not a mindless 3rd-person shooter. The importance of using cover is imperative. Without cover, stealth and acrobatic moves, you are likely to get killed within few seconds. Yet the satisfaction of pumping bullets into baddies is immensely gratifying. Newly implemented stealth attack is a nice addition to the original. Jumping from one ledge to anothor is exciting and platforming is all about how to get to the next area. Puzzle-solving is less complex but adequate enough for the game's main attraction is story and action. There are also a few stages where you are shooting for your life on moving stages.<br /><br />Acting is superb and real actors in motion-sensor suit were casted for acting and voice. One of few game that can really claim that the acting is top-notch along with superb voice-acting.  The score and the sound effects are incredible.  Hearing the main theme for the second time is a pure joy and an instant reminder that U2 is a sequel to an outstanding and highly successful blockbuster.<br /><br />U2 is a prime example where linearity, if well-structured, gives you more intense sense of urgency and excitement, something open-ended, free-forming games often lack. Furthermore, without the loading time, it actually feels as if it were, free-roaming game. Cutscenes are used by in-game graphics and they are blended seamlessly together. This is the closest thing to 'Interactive Movie' alongside the renowned MGS series. Throughout the game, the feeling of you being involved and immersed into the very game you play as if you were the main protagonist is constantly and continuously maintained.<br /><br />Naughty Dogs added co-op and up to 10 competitive multiplayer this time and main campaign spans 26 chapters in 12 to 15 hours single player campaign plus unlockable contents, hidden treasure hunts and trophies collection.<br /><br />Combat and movement is slightly more refined than the first one and stages are more diverse.  There are more contents and the game is also slightly longer than the first one.  The only downside, as a fan of action-adventure game, is just as the first game was, that the puzzle elements are too far and between and platforming still feels little too automated.  But Platforming is exciting nontheless and figuring out how to get to the next is puzzle itself, so as I said before, the main focus here is story and action and the pacing is incredible to make you forget the minor complains.  Everything on screen is pure joy to your eyes and graphical attention to detail like no other game currently in the market.<br /><br />Exciting action adventure game with awesome combat in breakneck-pace, quality script and great presentation, Uncharted 2 ventures further into where many games have gone before but few games succeed and places itself among the very best of video game.  Get it now.
      
