Best video game I've played
I'm a movie buff and not much of a gamer.  I have a ton of movies on blu-ray and a handful of PS3 games.  Reviews for this game were quite strong so I purchased this game on Amazon "blind".  <br /><br />So here are my observations from the perspective of a movie fan and a casual gamer:<br /><br />1.  This game is first and foremost FUN!  It actually has vibrant color, in contrast to the desaturated look of many action video games (even movies).  It doesn't take itself too seriously; it has a good story that's told well.  I was reminded of the first time I watched "Raiders of the Lost Ark".  For sheer entertainment value, I think it's hard to beat this game, even at the current full retail price.  My wife was watching me play and for the first time ever (with a video game), watched as a spectator and enjoyed it.  This game has changed her view on what the video game entertainment experience can be.<br /><br />2. This game knows what it's doing and it shows.  It takes a confident game to stop the action for a few minutes and just show Drake walking through a village; that particular sequence is absolutely gorgeous (and it's not even a cut scene).  There's no action; you're just experiencing the village, the people, the language, the color.  Amazing.  <br /><br />3.  This game is stellar from a technical point of view.  Superb graphics, great cinematic sound, convincing (for a video game) voice acting, movements, and facial gestures.<br /><br />4.  This game should raise the bar for others in the future.  As things stand now, I don't know if I'll be able to enjoy other games in quite the same way; my expectations now are probably way too high.  Even action movies from now on will probably seem like a passive experience.<br /><br />5. This game is a great value.  I've only played the single player mode; even then it's probably the best $50 that I've ever spent on an entertainment item.<br /><br />I can only hope we get more games such as this one in the future!
      
