Fantastic piece of gaming, should be 2009's game of the year.
This game officially sets the bar for "next gen" releases for years to come.  I am blown away with the amount of detail, depth, action, dedication etc that was put into this game.  I cannot stop promoting this game to friends who also play video games.  Reading all sorts of reviews is one of my main habits when purchasing any item.  This is my first review ever on Amazon, and this game is the main reason why I must start now.  I own the XBOX360, PS3 and Nintendo Wii.  And this game is just THAT AMAZING. Period.<br /><br />PROS:<br />-Ridiculous amount of detail put into this piece of work.<br />-Voice acting and character movement is top notch, I have never played/seen a game match this yet.<br />-RECORDED/SAVED GAMES FOR MULTIPLAYER.  I feel like most reviews have not covered this great feature that should be in all multiplayer games.  I love going back to multiplayer games to see what I might have missed out on.<br />-Unlockables! I love this feature, I feel like I'm back on Goldeneye 007 for Nintendo 64, chuckling at Donkey Kong head mode. Now I'm chuckling like a little kid at Doughnut Drake!<br />Freakin awesome<br />-Very minimal amount of bugs/glitches.  I can't say I've come across many, if any, games that are this level of quality.<br /><br />CONS:<br />-This game must have the record for people being saved with one hand from falling off cliffs, broken bridges, buildings etc.<br />-Sure nothing is perfect, but I got stuck in a big sprocket wheel thing.  That was probably the biggest glitch I ran into.  This is not a full on CON because it didn't take away from my near perfect experience with this game.  I've also had an enemy move super fast blurry-like crouching from side to side, like an agent in the Matrix. Again, this did not take away from my experience, I actually laughed at it in amusement.<br />-Doughnut Drake rests his arms in his stomach. His rifle sticks out at his upper back fat and lower back fat.  My favorite skin so far is a little off, but I still love it.<br /><br />In conclusion, I really only have two negative things to say about this game.  Naughty Dog, the game's developer, deserves a standing ovation for their work on this masterpiece.  I'm itching to jump back into campaign on hard difficulty after just beating Uncharted 2 on normal difficult at 2AM last night.  I love Uncharted 2 and I don't see myself putting it down for a long time.  I started off playing multiplayer on the demo/beta until the first 3 days of owning the game.  So I'm also itching to jump back to that.<br /><br />If you own a PS3, buy Uncharted 2. It's simply a no brainer.  I'd be very surprised to see a PS3 owner without this game in their library.<br /><br />If you don't own a PS3, this is a perfectly good reason to go out and get one. Like NOW.
      
