BEST Multiplayer Experience on the PS3 so far.
The game itself is an amazing addition to the video game genre and one of the best I've ever played.  There are countless elements to discuss about this game which make it so great, but it's all been said by HUNDREDS of others, so I won't beat it to death.  To summarize, the graphics will blow you away and give one of the most immersive game experiences on the market.  Sound is movie quality.  Gameplay is tight and responsive, and you feel like you're treking every step with Drake.  Story is solid.  Single player alone is worth the buy...<br /><br />But that's not why I'm writing this review.  I'm here to talk about the multiplayer, which has me playing night after night.  First off, The menu's for the MP are well done and easy to navigate.  There are 2 MP modes, Co-op & Competitive. Co-op is a mode where 3 people take on CPUs to do campaign missions, survival mode, or treasure hunter type games.  Competitive MP is where 2 teams of 5 square off in an array of different scenarios:  Deathmatch, King of the Hill, Turf War, Chain Reaction, Elimination, or Plunder.  Deathmatch is self explanatory, but it breaks down even FURTHER when you have all weapons, RPGs only, pistol & grenades only, Sniper rifle & pistole only... it's all good.  King of the Hill, Turf War, & Chain Reaction all have you capturing zones to give your team pts, each mode varying in gameplay.  Elimination basically has you trying to kill all members of the opposing team before they do in a best of 5 rounds.  Plunder puts a good spin on capture the flag, with the ability to THROW the flag (treasure).  All in all, each MP mode offers something unique and a great way to play online, be it with friends or solo.  The party system works great and allows you to easily set up a group of people ready to play games together.  Did I almost forget that there's a leveling system and upgrades for Co-op and Competitive Mode?  Plenty of Skins for your character?  Taunting?  All can be purchased with money made from playing online and add depth to the experience.  Naughty Dog is keeping things fresh with updates and downloadable maps and skins.. in fact there's supposed to be a new Map Pack being released 4/22!  Buy it already!!  You won't be disappointed!
      
