Flawless production
I'm not much of a gamer, I bought a PS3 largely to stream Netflix movies to my TV, play the occasional blu-ray, and maybe use it as a little media center. Until I picked up Uncharted 2, I'd been halfheartedly playing my way through GTA IV, and occasionally God of War. <br />This game was being demoed at Best Buy, and I happened to play it for about five minutes, where I was impressed with the graphics and gunplay mechanics, so I picked it up Friday after work.<br />It's now Sunday night, I just finished it, and I've been playing through the weekend nearly every waking minute. I've had to carve time out away from this game to do anything, it's completely amazing, engrossing, and entertaining. <br />The music is awesome and cinematic, the story is fun, the dialogue had me laughing out loud on occasion. The level design and visuals are breathtaking, every single environment is richly detailed, and I often found myself stopping gameplay just to look around the scenery, it's incredible. The graphics engine is so good, the cutscenes are rendered in real time, and they look like something out of Pixar. Gameplay is fluid and intuitive, the game on normal setting was challenging but never frustrating, and I never found a moment where I felt like I was putting in work to get to the next level. <br />This is as close as you're going to get to starring in your own Indiana Jones movie. Every element of the game was incredible, and although I'm sad the story is over, if the game took me any longer I'd be calling in sick to work to finish.
      
