Rockstar have done it again!
I've heard people say RDR is a GTA clone.  Though the game play is similar it's a good thing.  The missions are interesting and fun.  The mini games and challenges provide hours of fun outside of the story mode.  The hunting alone keeps me occupied for hours.  Then there's the poker, blackjack, liar's dice, five finger fillet, horse shoes, breaking horses and treasure hunting.  The honor and fame systems give it a kind of "RPG" feel though you don't "level up" but it definitely impacts how people react to you later in the game.  I love the random encounters and the other various side missions.  Did I mention the hunting?  Deer, buck, goats, big horn sheep, elk, buffalo, armadillos, coyotes, rabbits, foxes, wolves, grizzlies, eagles, hawks, vultures, crows, songbirds, bobcats and cougars.  Those are just the ones I've come across and I'm only about 50% through the game.  Every one of those animals can be "skinned" except for the birds whose feathers you can collect and turn their meat, hides, claws, horns, pelts and/or antlers in for money at general stores and/or gunsmith shops.  You can also loot people's bodies for money and you can collect their dropped weapons and ammo.  If you're not the kind of person that likes to complete a game to 100%, then this game may not be one of your favorites.  I personally love collectibles and side missions to distract me while I'm bored with the main story line.  Which is why I also loved Fallout 3.  I am looking very much forward to DLC for this game.  My only wish is that DLC would add more area to the map to explore further.  However, the map as it is now is HUGE.  I ran from the far bottom left corner of the map to the far upper right corner on a fast horse and it took me close to 10 - 15 minutes...but that's with stopping to skin a deer or two and stop to help a few folks who yelled for it.  <br /><br />In short...if you love open-world games with plenty more to do other than the main story line, GET THIS GAME!  Rockstar does it again!
      
