Return to the Old West: A Casual Gamer's Review
The last great game that I played on my PS3 was <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001E8VB6O">Batman: Arkham Asylum</a>. In fact, thinking about it I still smile a bit. I loved every minute of the adventure, and still recall climbing to the top of the clock tower, leaping off, and seeing how long I could soar. I didn't think that another game could come close to this adventure, but it turns out, I was wrong. I'm enjoying "Red Dead Redemption" just as much as Batman; for the graphic quality the shear adventure of the game, the ability to roam, the mini-games, and the total submersion of life in a Western town.<br /><br />The first time you get a chance to head out into the wilderness, you'll be impressed with the high quality realism of the game. Animals roam freely and are ripe for the hunting, but be careful of some angrier animals. I've been attacked by a cougar (and survived the tale) but didn't after a wolf pack attack. The missions John goes on are of the usual caliber, but they are fun, if not a bit repetitive. The bounty hunting pays a good price, especially if you get to lasso the criminal and hogtie him to carry him back alive.  You can play a variety of western games , my favorite is poker where, with the right clothes, you get to cheat.<br /><br />Overall, I found this game to be very easy to use. The design of the game is very intuitive, and you don't have to learn a bunch of fancy button moves to make things happen. Most importantly, it's just a lot of fun to slip into the old west for a hour a day, and ride my horse into the sunset, or rope a wild horse, or even chat it up with the saloon ladies.
      
