New Super Mario Bros Wii...Fantastic! More Please Nintendo!
This is a great game. I was apprehensive because it looked very similar to NSMBDS [a game I don't have, but the music and 'gist' was the same], But it's not. (I've heard someone say this is "2" - but I don't think it is either]. This is the sequel to Mario World*. Hands Down. [Spoilers below] <br /><br />Pros To Getting This Game:<br />1: it is really really fun.  The minute you enter the first world, you hear the re-vamped soundtracks, complete with bopping Goombas and dancing Koopas. <br /><br />2: Waggle Function thankfully kept to a minimum. <br /><br />3: Deliciously Hard. Not too hard that you want to throw your Wiimote across the room, but that special mix of "this should be so easy, I can get this, why is can't I do... OHHHhhhh" that you want in video games.<br /><br />4: Lack of "coasting: The one issue i HAD with Mario 3, and Mario World is that if you wanted, you can fly across the screen with a Pwing [M3] or with a Cape/Yoshi [World]. Not this time. PropellerMario has limited flight function, and while there is some Yoshi action - he stays behind while you move on.<br /><br />5: Return of the Koopalings: I always wondered where they went. <br /><br />6: Secrets Galore. There are several secret levels in a few worlds, matched up with secret exits where you couldn't BELIEVE where they are, and ... maybe.. other... secrets? to be found. <br /><br />7: SINGLE PLAYER FRIENDLY! If you don't have anyone to play with [such as I], do not fret. Nintendo made this as fun for 1 person as it clearly looks to be for 4. :)<br /><br />Cons. [not many]<br /><br />1: I would have liked t be able to play this as ANY character. You are locked as Mario [as a single player], and just by looking at 2/3 players you HAVE to be Mario. If they are going to go to the trouble of introducing 3 playable characters, at least let the player choose who they want to be at any stage of the game. <br /><br />2: Some of the secret hidden walls - a LOT secret. I know there is a way to tell; however, as someone who doesn't have NSMBDs.... not aware of them. Many of Lives were lost trying to find them.<br /><br />3: Super Guide: I don't like this concept of if you die a lot, you can have Luigi play it for you [you still have to play it yourself to count though]. It just symbolises: LOSER! to me.. (Yes I've triggered it. but i've never used it). <br /><br />4: Would have liked to have seen utalised the ability to use the classic controller. (of course, one can not waggle the classic controller - but, yeah, more games that lets you use it Nintendo would be great).<br /><br />So not a lot of cons. Honestly - pick this up and play it. If you have ANY reservations; rent it, but take my word for it, just buy it. <br /><br />I want to see more of these types of games, Nintendo... and maybe another Yoshi's Island WII!? :)
      
