Totally Awesome!
Much improved over the original Wii Sports, Wii Sports Resort takes Wii gaming fun to a whole new level.  With 12 Events instead of 5, you get some really fun and deep games.  My personal favorite has to be the sword fighting (kendo?), which can get very intense.  The controls for every game in here is obviously very well thought out, and feels quite natural.  Wii motion plus absolutely added a whole dimension of accuracy to the gameplay.  About the only mini-game that didn't feel like it had motion-plus accuracy was maybe bowling, but it was at least as good as the original, so not really a minus.   Highly recommended for anyway who has a wii, and especially if you enjoyed the original Wii sports (even just a little bit).
      
<!-- BOUNDARY -->
Tremendous fun with friends/family or alone!
This game is flat out fun and awesome!  <br /><br />My wife received it as a gift for her birthday and we have not stopped playing it since.  In fact, we have had over twenty people playing at a party one afternoon and night (ages ranged from 23 to 87) and every loved it. (grandma even rolled a strike her first time playing 100-pin bowling).  The last three days we have had friends and family come over for Wii Sports Resorts action and nobody wants to go home! (it's cool because we now have all our friends and family as Mii's on our console).<br /><br />We bought an extra Wii Motion Plus so we can go head-to-head on some games but many games allow you to share one controller between 4 players (turn based games like bowling, golf, frisbee and archery).<br /><br />There are twelve distinct games in Wii Sports Resort and within them are several different modes.  Standouts for me are:<br /><br />Swordplay:  Three modes (VS, Speed Slice, and Showdown)...showdown is my favorite, you face a hoard of Mii's rushing you and you have to go 'Conan' on them.<br /><br />Frisbee:  Love the Frisbee Dog (accuracy competition...I play a few rounds after a stressful day at work and it's very relaxing, and the challenge is tall because it's tough to keep building on your high scores)<br /><br />Archery:  Great fun with the nunchuck, use the remote as the Bow and the nunchuck to knock your arrow and pull back on the string.  You shoot at targets at increasing range..very challenging.<br /><br />Bowling:  So far I've only played 100-Pin...that's bowling with 100 pins...how cool is that (especially when you get a strike and knock them all down)<br /><br />Air Sports:  Flying and Skydiving....Flying is very low key, you pilot an airplane (solo, but there is a two-player dog-fight mode) and are challenged to visit 80 points of interest on the island (some require you fly through caves 'in' the island).  Skydiving is also low-key and fun...the challenge is to link up mid-air with other skydivers so you can have your photo taken, turn to face the camera to show smiling faces for more points. At the end you get to see the photos of you and all your friends from the jump.<br /><br />Issues:  Having read some unfavorable reviews I'd like to give you my take.<br /><br />Controller calibration:  For the most part we have had no serious problems, although it's true, after some time and wild play, the calibration gets a little wonky.  This is easily fixed by either pointing the remote at the screen and press the D-button (direction button at the front of the remote) or press the '+' button and set the remote on a flat surface for ten seconds so the gyros can settle down.<br /><br />Graphics:  They are on par with many Wii games like Wii Fit, Wii Play, Wii Sports..etc...The Wii is not under any circumstance going to look like a PS3 hooked to a HD TV.  Could the graphics on Wii Sports Resort be more detailed, probably (some games your Mii only has hands holding the sword or paddle but no arms), but as it is, they are good graphics and the game play is smooth and fast considering all the physics models programed in for each game.  Personally, I'd sacrifice top-end graphics for a fun game that runs and plays smooth<br /><br />I am totally satisfied and love this game as much as Mario Kart Wii (my other favorite).  It's tons of fun, especially with friends (which is why I love Wii more than PS3 or XBox, much more multi-player/family oriented and shared fun is always the best in my book).<br /><br />I think this game will be a solid addition to your library especially if you have people to enjoy it with.
      
