Don't notice it, doesn't get in the way
I don't have much to say about this product, which is a good thing, since you actually don't want to notice this accessory, and you don't want it getting in the way.<br /><br />We've been using this with Wii Sports Resort, and based on the extreme fun level of Wii Sports Resort, I'd say this accessory is a success.<br /><br />My 11 year old son did comment right away that it made the Wiimote a bit bigger, but he never commented on it again. I didn't really notice any difference, and we quickly got deep into the game, not thinking about the controller (which is how it should be).<br /><br />One surprise was that Wii Sports Resort actually required the MotionPlus for each player (I incorrectly assumed it was optional), so be sure to purchase one of these for each player.  If you want to have 3 or 4 player games in Wii Sports Resort, for example, then you will need 3 or 4 of these. It's not an option to just have one player have an inferior experience. Similarly, you need 3 or 4 Nunchuks if you want 3 or 4 player games for some of the games.<br /><br />My only complaint is that it seems this would have to drain some Wiimote battery, and the Wiimotes already suck batteries way too quickly.  I suppose I just need to invest in some rechargeable batteries.<br /><br />Finally, note that there is a temporary special bundle of Wii Sports Resort that includes TWO of these MotionPlus accessories, so be sure to shop for the bundles first, before buying these individually.
      
