Great combo pack in a cool color
There's not a whole lot to say about this controller set that you wouldn't already know from previously using the standard white controllers.  I will, however, say that the black glossy finish on the face of the controller is extremely attractive, and brings a whole new life to the Wii controller.  This combo pack includes the MotionPlus attachment which, while not currently supported by a lot of games, will be seeing more and more use in the near future.  It also includes 2 opaque black Nintendo branded rubber "jackets" for the controller (1 for use with the MotionPlus, 1 without), a black wrist strap, and 2 AA batteries (a nice little bonus in a world where companies are usually cutting corners).<br /><br />Like all Nintendo hardware products, this thing is built like a rock.  While using the rubber jackets is not required, it will help to extend the life of these controllers even further (although I'm still using my two white controllers that I got on launch day for the Wii, never put them in a jacket and they're going strong).<br /><br />My biggest complaint is that if Nintendo is selling this product as a bundle, why can't they simply build that MotionPlus functionality into the original controller's form factor?  The added width from the MotionPlus attachment forces you to remove the attachment whenever you want to play games that require you to hold the controller horizontally, like New Super Mario Bros.  It just seems silly to feel like I always have to swap the attachments on and off whenever I want to play something like Wii Sports Resort.<br /><br />Despite this one little issue, this bundle is a fantastic value, I highly purchasing one (or more) of these if you don't yet have 4 controllers for the Wii but would like to round out your collection.
      
