I Got Some Exercise!
I bought Wii Fit Plus with a little trepidation, but I figured for the price (I already have Wii Fit and the Balance Board), I wouldn't lose much if the game was awful.  I am glad I bought it.  Like others mentioned, the Wii Fit got old pretty quickly; I've had it for a year, but only used it regularly for the first 6 months I had it.  When I bought Sport Active at the end of May, I never even thought of the Balance Board or Wii Fit.  However, Wii Fit Plus had definitely reunited me with the Balance Board.  <br /><br />I won't mention all the particulars because others have so generously used their time to talk about the details.  Nonetheless, I will say this: Wii Fit Plus got me sweating!  I use Sport Active on the hard level, 6 days a week.  I will now use it only 4-5 days a week and use Wii Fit Plus on the weekends.  The first time I "played" I picked my own routine and it ended up being 37 minutes long.  By the time I was done, I was sweating very heavily (and I'm in pretty good condition and not overweight).  I really liked how you can pick what you want to work on in your custom routine.<br /><br />If you are on the fence, I would say "Buy it," especially if you already have a Balance Board.  For the price, there's almost nothing to lose and definitely fun and some fitness to gain.
      
