Fantastic addition to the God of War franchise
Let me just start out by saying that I bought my PSP on launch day.  After playing Lumines to death, just like everyone else, my PSP was nothing more than an overpriced paperweight 2 years or so.  This God of War game was honestly the first piece of compeling software that made me want to buy a new game for the system.  To be fair, I am a fan of the franchise and have played through both 1 and 2 multiple times.  I was very concerned that the control scheme would not translate well to the PSP.  Boy, was I ever wrong.  This game has all the polish of the other 2 games in the franchise and works beautifully on the PSP.  The controls are crisp and precise.  The combo system is completely intact and adds several new weapons and magic items to your arsenal.  The only complaint I have about this game is that it did not come out a year or two sooner.  If it had, The portable landscape would likely be very different.  This game is the killer app that Sony has sorely needed for the PSP.  Since playing this game, I have fallen in love with my PSP all over again.  I have probably purchase 10 or 12 games since beating this and have found that there are many good titles out there now.  If you are a fan of God of War, buy this game.  You will not be disapointed.
      
