I'm an accountant who as of 2007 has fallen in love with "gadgets". I own 3 iPods, an iFlip video camera, an XBox360, and a Sprint TOUCH cell phone.<br /><br />I bought a PSP just to have a portable video player that would play all my downloaded rap videos and not require headphones at all times. I recommend buying a protective cover for this right away.<br /><br />PROS:<br /><br />-Plays movies, videos, music, and games and does so with quality. I was impressed with the sound and videos that were recorded in good quality, played in good quality.<br />-Hooks up to everything. I watch the videos in my car and plug it into the same wire I use to listen to my iPod thru my car stereo. I am able to use the composite wires to hook it up to tv's in hotels when I'm travelling. I can plug it into all my friends stereos thru the headphone jack and DJ house parties and gatherings.<br />-Easy to use. With the media manager I select the songs or videos I want to load and it converts them and puts them in alphabetical order for me in my PSP. My Windows Vista has issues with iTunes but has no problems with the media manager or media player to load songs.<br />-You get bang for your buck. I bought mine on sale for $169.99. I did buy a few add ons with speakers, cover, composite wire and media manager but no item cost over $20. My iPod Touch was $399, my 360 was $399, and my cell phone was $300 so this was a bargain for me and what I'm used to spending on these kind of items.<br /><br />I own only 1 game, Tiger Woods 2008, and only play it for a few minutes here and there but it looks nice and is fun to play. I own 0 UMD movies for it so I can't review that feature. I was a HUGE iPod fan and very loyal to that product but the PSP is #1 today and my favorite gadget right now. I have only owned my PSP 2 weeks but so far no complains or issues after I figured out how to keep it clean.
      
