A really nice system
9/10/2008<br />I purchased the PSP several months back, and I have to say I really enjoy it.  I can't complain about the number of titles for it...  it has the titles I'm interested in, and that's what counts.  Over all, the graphics and sound are outstanding.  I haven't played with the other features much, but it's nice to know they're there.  My only complaints are small...  The battery life is a bit short (but I usually play at home, so no real bother for me...)  Also, this is a new model, which is smaller than the old.  Unfortunately there are several nice accessories still available for the old PSP, but they won't fit this one.  So it's buyer-beware when shopping for these.<br /><br />Update: 10/2/2009<br />So, I'm still rocking the same PSP, and it's still working like a champ.  Over the past year, I've gotten a little more aware of the capabilities of this little system.  It truly is a powerhouse!  Granted you won't be using it for regular web browsing, the internet capabilities are still quite nice to have.  Mostly for firmware upgrades and downloadable content from the PlayStation Store.  Downloading the games has 2 advantages:  Longer battery life, and fewer things to carry around (an 8GB memory stick holds at least 8 games...)  Sony was even kind enough to start releasing old PS1 games for download.  I'm currently playing through FFVII.  As far as the multimedia capabilities go, I still use my laptop for watching DVDs on the road, and my MP3 player for music.  This system is simply too small to use for movies, and too big to carry around for music.  But, neither of those were reasons for my purchase, so I'm still very happy.
      
