Best PSP Case
The PSP Phat Logitech Case was made awhile back and it did not fit the Slim PSP. Logitech has answered our calls and made a slim version on the case. Overall, the case is great. The psp fits snuggly in the case and provides great protection. The cover also flips 270 degrees so you can use it as a stand. All buttons can be accessed and the case locks shut, so the case won't open unexpectedly. The memory card slot and the USB connection will be blocked, so you will have to take out the PSP to access those areas. If you have an extended battery, you can also use this case. The best part about this product is the able to customize it with your very own image. You can place the images on the back of the case between the rubber and the case outside. They will provide you with a template to use so you can print out your own creations. I personally recommend using an ex-acto knife to cut out the images. Lastly, your PSP can nest itself inside the case and can be used as a grip..it works really well.<br /><br />Pros:<br />+Great Protection (Inside + Outside)<br />+Small Enough To Be Taken Anywhere<br />+Customize Images<br />+Buttons are All Accessible (Expect for the WLAN Switch/Memory Stick/USB)<br />+Can Be Used as a Stand<br />+PSP Can Nest Inside and Be Used as a Grip<br />+Looks Very Nice<br /><br />Cons:<br />-Template That Comes Inside Package Isn't 100% Accurate<br /><br /><br />There aren't many cons out there to deal with this product. If you need the convenience and protection, I would highly recommend getting this product!<br />
      
