A must wear, hear, use, and buy
JLab has presented a great product. Comfort, sound quality, durability, and affordability in order are the variables I use to choose earphones.  The J3s excel in all variables which translate to success in my view.<br />The level of comfort provided by the earpieces is unexpected and on par with pricier earphones.  I wear mine sometimes for eight to nine hours a day.  Sound quality is superb.  The highs and lows have been engineered to sound as they should; crystal clear with rich tones for treble, midranges, and bass.  No attribute overwhelms, but all are extremely impressive.  Durability is a must and the J3s deliver.  I twist; pull, and crush wires during my work day (by accident of course) and the J3s have remained resilient.  The no tangle/no kink wire casing has played a major role in the survival of these earphones for me and I'm sure will continue to keep them healthy for some time to come.  The price point for these earphones is a steal.  They are deserving of a heftier price.  I am grateful to JLab for making this quality of earphone available at this price.<br />The only con if it indeed is a con I have about the earphones is that right and left earpieces are not marked (at least not on my set).  It has not made a difference in my listening pleasure and may have made the task of placing the earpieces in my ear easier.  I don't have to hunt for the little R and the little L.  <br />
      
