Best earbuds I've owned
First let me state that all the low-rating complaints about bass, treble and tin problems are absolutely true - if you never take the time to figure out how the things are supposed to be worn. These require that you choose the correctly sized cover (4 different options are included), and fit them snugly inside your ear. Let them dangle like you would other earbuds, and they won't sound as good because they're not designed to work that way.<br /><br />Once you get it right, the sound is of immense quality. Bass is deep, and can even be too much at high volumes. The mids come off very slightly scooped on some tracks, but not enough to complain when you're talking about earbuds. The highs are as crisp as you could want them to be. <br /><br />The best part about them is that they let you listen to the music and nothing else. I've never gotten even a hint of cord noise, and, using the proper cover for my ear size, I can't hear people talking right next to me. Even just this morning I noticed a faint background track on a song I've listened to 100 times before, and that was at half volume on an iPod while standing on the 8th Ave. sidewalk in NYC. At the same volume, you barely hear an incoming subway train while standing on the platform.<br /><br />I've had literally hundreds of different pairs of headphones: Bose, Koss, SennHeiser, Ultrasone, Beyerdynamic, you name it. Put these J-labs up against any other earbuds, and they win every time. And for this price, there really isn't a question of choice.<br /><br />Plus, these completely make up for their lackluster J1 and J2 sets.
      
