Great buy!
I tend to buy mid level headphones/earbuds (20-50$). I prefer having higher sound quality over the "free" ipod buds. Still, I can't justify spending more for earbuds than I did for my ipod, especially when the lifespan of electronics in my house (between my toddler and the cat) is about 6 months. I am no audiophile, but the J3's are far better than anything I've ever bought. As others have mentioned, the high notes are a little harsh before the "burn in" period. Even without the "burn in", these headphones stand out in every way. <br /><br />After opening the package, my first impression was how light these felt. The body is a solid piece of metal and feels very sturdy. The cord looks woven, but covered in a translucent rubber coating that seems strong. They form a seamless seal in my ear. Even though these aren't marketed as "noise canceling" they block out noise pretty well. I share an office with a "loud talker" that spends a good part of the day on the phone and these help a lot. <br /><br />Several other reviews mention that these cause excessive rubbing noise, due to the stiffness of the cord and the seal formed with the ear. However, I find this to be no worse than other earphones. I might be a bit biased here, as the earphones that these are replacing (due to failure) are the Altec Lansing earphones with the cloth cord. The friction-related noise was unbearable at times. <br /><br />I wouldn't pay ~80$ (listed as the retail price), but these are an amazing buy at 30$. <br />
      
