My favorite headphones, period.
I am EXTREMELY picky about sound. I have spent a couple of years and many hundreds of dollars searching for the perfect headphones, and with the M40s I have found them.<br />They are the only headphones I have encountered with a perfect frequency response. Their FR graph is literally a horizontal line from 5Hz to 28KHz! A truly incredible achievement. As a result, the sound is flawless, with every part of the audible spectrum represented and nothing masked by anything else.<br />There is no distortion whatsoever, none.<br />There is a truly microscopic level of detail.<br />The soundstage is unusually large for closed headphones, and imaging is pinpoint precise as well as 3-dimensional.<br />Instrument tones and voices are perfectly natural and lifelike, just like being there in the studio or at the concert. I can here every word of the lyrics (even by mumblers like REM), and can easily pick out individual voices within a large chorus.<br />The only shortcoming is comfort, and it is not bad, just not as good as ultra-comfy open phones such as AD700s. Comfort is FAR better with these than M50s.<br /><br />I cannot more highly reccomend any pair of headphones (and I have heard many, some far more expensive. In particular, these sound better than Sennheiser HD280s and HD595s, AKG K701s, Audio Technica's own AD700s and AD900s, and Denon AH-D5000s.)<br /><br />Buy these, you will NOT regret it!
      
