Had a great idea some time ago, why don't I listen to audio books when I'm working out at the fitness center?  Well it is a good idea except when there is a lot of distracting room noise, especially near-by conversations and TVs. I looked into noise-canceling headphones and bought the Bose QC 15. Well it is the literal night and day difference.  The constant sounds of machines are all but eliminated and periodic noises like conversations are well muted.   The audio is just fine with good dynamic range and bass response. $300 is a hell a of a lot of money for earphones but these things really work.
      
