Exceptional noise cancelling, exceptional sound quality; definately worth the price.
After researching the Sennheiser PXC450s and these headphones, I chose the Bose QC15s. <br /><br />Why I chose the Bose:<br />-The sound quality is fantastic.<br />-Both Sennheiser and Bose were very comparable in price and specifications, with the Sennheisers being slightly larger but the padding on the Bose being more comfortable.  <br />-The Bose has a longer battery life of approx 36 hours (40 hours and counting here).  <br />-The Bose can be used only for noise canceling, which they do extraordinarily well, and the cord detaches (convenient for sleeping on flights).  I've noticed a slight pressure in my right eardrum while not listening to music; the pressure is slight and isn't enough to cause discomfort. There is no pressure when listening to music.<br />-The case is well-constructed and has room for carrying an mp3 player and additional AAA batteries. <br /><br />After running 40 hours of "noise" through the headphones, the sound quality and frequency response does seem to be greatly improved, with a more realistic experience, almost like being center-stage at a concert.  And, after 40 hours, the original AAA battery that came with the headset is still powering the noise-canceling feature.  For truly enjoying music, these are the headphones that I would recommend.<br /><br />
      
