A slightly different perspective
I usually do not review stuff, but I rely on the reviews to make selections.  I am vocal about not writing reviews without ample experience with the product when I rarely provide feedback to a reviewer.  So why did I stop lurking and decide to write a review?  Why am I breaking my own rule about spending some time with an item before telling others to buy it (or not)?  Simply, I am really impressed with my introduction to this product.  I have never had noise canceling earphones.... ever.  It is for that reason I am writing this.  If you are not familiar with this technology, I am here to tell you these things really do the job!  I sit in a cubicle that is at one of the noisiest parts of the building I occupy.  I sit across from a data center and its constant din; on a main aisle that has constant traffic with cell phone and hallway conversations and impromptu meetings; cube neighbors that talk loudly and in different languages (Non-English speakers talk even louder, thinking no one can understand them anyhow); offices across from me whose occupants will not close their doors for meeting or conference calls, not that I am going to tell them to! Add to that the fact that I write for my main job.  This means I need to read docs and write docs all day!  For this there is a substantial concentration requirement. I tell you I was going nuts here.  But not now, nope, not now.  These earphones have saved my job and my sanity.  $300.00 is a mere price to pay (trust me; I am sucking wind at the cost (no lunches for a spell)). So, if you have the price and the need, spend the money and save all the anguish I suffered.  Thanks to all of you who took the time to help me decide. Like I said earlier, I really rely on the reviews that users provide. I have to add that I find the music through these crisp, clear and alive.  Good balance of sound, and the quieting circuits make it seem so much better.  WOW!
      
