Best computer speakers I've ever heard :-)
In the computer store, I had some doubt as to whether these tiny little speakers would have good sound quality.  After all, they are roughly 2 inches tall x 6 inches wide (not counting the woofer), and for many years, I used Boston Acoustic stereo speakers that were roughly 2 feet tall x a foot wide.  I needn't have worried.  I easily hooked these speakers up to my computer and the sound system is awesome!  Far better than those Boston Acoustic speakers that were state of the art in the `80s, and better than the 7 year-old Labtec speakers I've used (which are pretty good.)  I can't detect any distortion in the sound, and it has a 3-D feel to it.  Music sounds fabulous on it.  Highly recommended.<br />
      
