Outstanding
I'll preface by admitting I'm not an audiophile since before birth, I don't own a $35,000 CD player with 36x oversampling and error correction provided courtesy of NASA and no, I don't have perfect pitch. However, I do enjoy good music over a good sound system and was blown (completely) by the Bose Lifestyle system (DVD/music storage is moronic but the sound is something made in heaven). For now though and despite the reviews claiming tinniness I decided to buy the Companion 5. I mainly listen to music but I wanted this system instead of the Companion 3 because I wanted to give complete sound control to Bose (these have a built in sound card).<br />The sound is simply outstanding. I'm listening right now to Souad Massi (look her up) and for the sound to be any warmer, closer, immediate she would have to perform right here in my room. Eric Clapton's guitar sounds absolutely real, just fantastic. I toned down the bass a little but otherwise did nothing.<br />I haven't tested the surround effect yet since I don't really watch movies or play games on the computer. For music, I would give this 6 stars if I could. Incidentally - the setup is absolutely trivial. If you are not color blind and lost your sense of touch (either will do), setup takes 30 seconds flat.<br />Here's what I would improve (I'm a techie, we can always improve): since this system basically takes over the sound card, it should have had a mic input. There are good reasons not to use a mic with speakers (echo being the primary) but the choice should be mine. Not having a remote is something that doesn't bother me, but could bother some people. Lastly and common to all systems but a real pet peeve - attaching headphones to the controller unit instantly mutes the speakers. I would much rather have my headphones constantly attached and a switch to control what happens - taking cables in and out all the time breaks connectors. All that said, I can't express how much I'm enjoying the sound coming out of these puppies. And should you care - they also look really great. All the pretentiousness Bose could muster :-)
      
