Very good speakers for the money
Let me preface this by saying I am extremely picky about music, and have about 20k of very carefully selected audio gear :)<br /><br />These speakers will not satisfy the audiophile, but they are without a doubt the best multimedia speakers I've ever heard.  Crisp highs, thick and tight lows, however the mids are slightly under-represented, but thats to be expected due to the small size of the diaphrams.  The stereo image is a bit strange as well, its not bad, but does take some getting used to.<br /><br />Also, these speakers are *extremely* directional, when setup correctly they basically sound good in one spot.  Even tilting the speakers slightly makes a huge difference in the sound.  The problem with the mids can be minimized to a very acceptable level by placing the speakers correctly.  This is an advantadge to me personally as  I use them in my office and the sound doesn't carry as much as a set of bookshelf speakers.  These speakers also sound better at mid to high volumes then lower ones.<br /><br />Overall -- I'm of the opinion that if speakers sound bad, it doesn't matter how cool they look.  However, when somethign looks good and functions well, its just that much better.  <br /><br />One last note == these speakers are good enough to make low bitrate MP3s sound like the four letter word they are.  If you're investing in a decent pair of speakers, you should consdier encoding your music to a high bitrate MP3 or medium to high bitrate Ogg (of course you paid for your music, so you can do that...right? hah)
      
