Spectacular!!
Very easy to set up, works great, and looks beautiful.  It sounds perfect, not off in the slightest.  As far as the power, it's loud enough for a very loud listening level, and loud enough to fill a floor for a casual party, but not loud enough for a dance party or to fill the entire house.  The bass is actually overpowered if you turn it all the way up.  I keep it at the mid-point and it's just right.  You don't need 5.1 for MP3's and virtually all CD's, because they're not in 5.1.  BTW the two towers have a rubbery base which prevents them from slipping.  The subwoofer cylinder has a bluish light that makes it look sci-fi.  Put it under the table just like the manual says.<br /><br />The one slight criticism I would make is that there's no way to quickly turn down the volume on the speakers themselves.  However, what I do is to keep the speakers close to the max, and then to use Apple's Frontrow remote (or the keyboard) to adjust the system volume.  You can quickly go from zero to max and back and again that way with a couple of pushes of the up or down button on the remote or on the keyboard.<br /><br />The price is very reasonable.  I can't think of a speaker system for my computer that I would prefer to this one in terms of sound quality or appearance, and so if you're going to spend $1,500 for a computer, spending 10% of that or $150 for superior speakers is well worth it!
      
