Harman Soundsticks
There was nothing truly wrong with my previous pair of Boston Acoustic speakers, they were just about 8 years old and I was looking for something that took up less space. I have always had my eye on the Soundsticks, and like the majority of the other reviewers...these do not disappoint. The subwoofer is big, but as they recommend, it's on the floor under my desk, so I freed up a a nice bit of space not having a subwoofer and two speakers on my desktop. They have a clean, simple design. The volume buttons, located at the bottom of the front of one of the sticks, were hard to find, as they are so small they are barely visible...not a problem, just a fact. They are very sensitive and it takes almost no pressure to adjust.  The sound is rich and complex with great bass...I hear new things in the music I've been listing to for years. All and all, a great speaker system for a great price.
      
