Works great!
pd = f<br />p  = 3.1416 (pi)<br />d  = diameter of tire in millimeters<br />f  = wheel factor<br /><br />I was a little confused at first, but after fiddling around with it for awhile, and reading what others have said about it here, I finally got it setup right, and it works great. Like others have already said, you need to get the proper wheel factor entered. You can figure out the wheel factor with the above formula, or just measure the circumference of your tire and convert that to millimeters to get the wheel factor.
      
