No Problems
Just received the Klean Kanteen shoulder sling for $5.50 w/ free 2 day shipping. Despite many negative reviews, I figured how bad could it be for the money? It came in the same box as the Klean Kanteen 27 ounce bottle I had also ordered, and both were in protective poly bags. With trepidation I started the alleged horrific process of placing the bottle in the sling. I don't know what is different about the sling I got, but after carefully lining it up with the bottom of the bottle, I simply pulled evenly on the straps and it slipped right over the bottle! It is a snug fit, but that is good. It won't slip out on the trail, and since it is hanging at your side, you don't need to take it out of the sling to drink, just unscrew the cap and go for it. The cap threads on easily,and has a soft(neoprene?) gasket to insure a good seal. The bottle is sturdy yet light, and with a very attractive finish(I chose the black), and the best thing is no more crappy plastic taste! Both the bottle and the sling are five stars as far as I am concerned, and I am going to order another bottle and sling in the 40 ounce size.
      
