Nice accessory for Klean Kanteen bottle
I recently became interested in stainless steel water bottles for purely pragmatic reasons. After determining the 40 oz. Klean Kanteen appeared to meet my needs, I investigated the various options. The sling holders made specifically to fit the bottle was a welcome option to allow hauling the bottle around with me. Until recently I've carried re-used water bottles until they became worn from the constant use. I was a bit concerned about the fit of the sling based on some of the reviews I'd read, but I found it took me only about 30 seconds to slide the sling onto the Kanteen (no directions needed). The adjustable strap is handy to allow me to change the length as I may need. Since I initially made the strap relatively short, there was a foot or so of strap that needed to be dealt with. I just folded it up in an accordion fashion and wrapped a couple rubber bands around it.Everything fits well and the strap allows me to hang on to the bottle along with a computer bag, portfolio and whatever else I may be hauling from one meeting to another. I'm sure if I think enough I can come up with some negatives about the sling, but for the price and functionality it provides, I'm quite happy with the product.
      
