A Great Time-Saver!
The floor in my office is rough exposed-aggregate concrete, comprised of a pebbly uneven surface that traps sand, crumbs, and other fine debris and is almost impossible to clean with a standard upright vacuum.  I also have a golden retriever that sheds constantly.  I had finally resorted to using a bulky shopvac to clean this floor, which was a hassle and took up a lot of storage space in the closet.<br /><br />I thought I would give the Dirt Dog a try, though I was skeptical that it would be able to clean such a rough and irregular surface.  After I charged it up, I turned it loose on the floor and watched it go to work.  To my surprise, it not only was able to handle the rough surface but it did a fantastic job of cleaning.  When it did encounter an especially bumpy section of the floor, it would stop, back up an inch or so, turn a few degrees, and take another run at it.  Most often it only took one extra try to get over any extra bumpy spot on the floor.<br /><br />After about an hour, I shut it off and flipped it over to clean it.  The dust bin was full of dog hair, paper clips, plastic bread wrapper clips, push pins, and pieces of dog kibble.  The bin was easy to empty and the brush was also easy to pop out and remove the dog hair that had wrapped around it.<br /><br />The floor looks great and I'm really satisfied with this purchase!
      
