Pleasantly surprised
I relay heavily on other's opinions and thought that the bissell steam mop had the highest user ratings.  However, I was still skeptical at how well it would actually work.  My entire house is tile, except for the bedrooms, and I bemoan the fact that I must vacuum then mop the floor every week.  It usually takes over an hour - time I don't have.  So, I am always looking for an easier way. <br /><br />Well, I found it.  The system is so easy!  Really!  All you have to do is put the water in - wait 15 second and presto you're on your way to a clean floor.  No buckets, no wringing the mop, no dirty water to be changed.  Now granted I have three kids under five and a dog so my floors are never, ever clean.  So for the first cleaning I held down the steam button for the entire floor.  And then dried it with a towel.  But, the second cleaning I only used the steam about half the time and the floor dried quickly and relatively streak free.  <br /><br />Now the mop cloth does become saturated if you have a large area to clean, so you might want to switch it out half way through.  I ordered extra mop cloths for this very reason.  However, they are very easy to put on - you just have to wait for them to cool off a little.<br /><br />Pros - easy to use, much quicker than mopping, can easily get under cabinets and other low furniture, chemical free, does an amazing job cleaning, quiet enough to use when the kids are sleeping, easy to use for quick clean up jobs<br /><br />Cons -  it probably cleans almost too well - now I can see where the grout wasn't cleaned off well enough when the tile was laid.  Also, the mop cloths could be a little more durable.  There are several small holes in the one (it might be because I pushed down on the mop too hard the first time I used it, because there are only holes in that one mop cloth - I've since found that it cleans just as well without pushing down on it)<br />However, it still cleans like a champ! <br />Highly recommend!
      
