Bissell 1867-7 Steam Mop
This mop is absolutely wonderful! I've never cared for mops because they don't get the corners and edges to my satisfaction, so I've spent a lifetime on hands and knees.  The Bissell mop is unlike any other.  It does an excellent job...even in tight corners in the bathroom! The terry cloth mop cover wraps up and around the mop head, so even the edges get clean. The mop cover is sturdy and durable...just toss it in the laundry and it's fresh and clean for the next use. They even include a spare! Unlike other mops that use disposable mop covers, future costs on this one are minimal.  These are heavy duty mop covers, so I suspect they'll last at least a year.  Nearly my entire first floor is ceramic tile, so I used to spend 30-45 minutes washing the floor.  I can now sail through it in 10 minutes...making it easy to do a quick clean mid-week if I want to.  I would not recommend this for wood floors; it would get too wet and would result in warping the wood over time. Ideal for ceramic, marble, or vinyl, though. This was the best investment I've made in a long time! It's constructed of good quality materials (not flimsy and breakable), yet very lightweight so that using it is not a chore. This is my first Bissell product, so I'm very impressed.
      
