If you have tile, throw your mops away
I have a TON of tile in my house.  Mopping takes forever and is, quite frankly, just gross.  The Swiffer Wet Jet goes through too many pads and solution.  Both are a task and a half, and the floors are left streaky and dull.<br /><br />This item was on back order when I placed my order.  First it was for 3-4 weeks, then 5-6.  I almost canceled, but realized that Amazon.com had the best price going, and since I was still Swiffering and mopping, I wasn't going to do anything different if I did cancel because ordering it any other place would cost me more than double without the cost of shipping.<br /><br />It arrived a week ago and I am so impressed.  I had read the reviews about the "short cord", and have to say that it isn't that short, but not quite long.  No big deal.  Invest in a grounded extension cord and this will not be a problem at all.<br /><br />The manufacturer recommends distilled water for most efficient steam production, and better filter performance.  We have very hard water, so I decided to spend the buck on a gallon of distilled water.  Given how much you spend on cleaners in general, it's not much.  You will be surprised at the size of the water tank on the Green Tea.  You will also be surprised at how far that small tank of water goes.  It doesn't take much to do a lot - I've yet to use a full tank on my entire downstairs floor (this includes 2 regular bathrooms, a master suite bathroom, kitchen, dining, entry, foyer and laundry room).  I am most happy about the fact that I will never have to buy or smell Mr. Clean, Pine Sol, and/or Lysol again.  Oh, the savings =)  A gallon of water will last well over a month, if not 6 weeks.<br /><br />This little thing heats up in minutes, and goes the distance.  No streaks, no chemicals, and no headache.  The chenille pads are soft, absorbent and easy to change.  The steam is uber-hot and dissolves grime, dirt and all the other sticky stuff that finds itself onto a kitchen floor in seconds.  Best of all, it weighs next to nothing, and pivots well (it reaches behind my toilets with ease).  When I mop now, it literally takes 15 minutes or less, and there's no mess to clean up when I am done.  I just remove the pad, wrap the cord and store the steam mop.<br /><br />This has been a blessing.  This task is no longer a chore for me, and I don't mind "mopping" a few times a week now.  I would strongly recommend this to anyone who has lots of tile (I already have), and not a lot of time to mop.  If you have kids and dogs, this is a dream.  (Did I mention how quiet it is?)<br /><br /><br />P.S.  You can order the replacement filters and chenille pads directly from Bissell.  The cost (and the shipping) is far less than any e-tailer, even the one who sells through amazon.com. If you have  a lot to mop, you will need to change the pad when it accumulates enough dirt and gets too wet, or it will begin to streak.  Again, it takes seconds and is easy and painless.  (All other parts and accessories for this machine are also at bissel.com for much less, too.)<br />
      
