Works well!
I purchased this steamer about 8 months ago. I does a good a job. I have a lot of hardwood floors, including in the kitchen and it cleans up the typical stuff around the stove, dishwasher and sink. Works well on hard surfaces like tile or laminate flooring. It does not clean the mortar on tile. Have not really tried it on carpet. On hardwood some effort is required as the damp pad tends have more resistance on wood than with tile or other surfaces. The steamer takes about 5 minutes to heat up.<br /><br />I bought the Monster unit over others based on reviews and what appears to be better overall construction, except as noted below.<br /><br />The handle on the unit I purchased broke in the middle this weekend. It was very difficult to keep the top and bottom parts screwes together tightly. I called the customer service number - 888-896-8786 - and they offered to send a new, redesigned handle. Apparently if the lower part of your handle is curved it is more prone to snapping in the middle. They explained they have had numerous complaints like mine. The new handle with instructions is suppose to arrive later this week, free of charge.<br /><br />UPDATE: I received the new handle today, one week from the dat I call the distributor. Unlike the original handle which was curved and screwed together in the middle, the new handle is straight and is a telescoping "one piece" design. The metal used seems to be a little heavier as well. I tried it out briefly and the new design seems to overcome the problem with the original which was screwed together in the middle. The old one would become loose where it came together and eventually snapped from the back and forth movement and pressure. The new one does not become "loose" and doesn't flex. Much better. If you have the old handle and it hasn't broken yet do yourself a favor and call to get the new one.
      
