Still a great magazine
My favorite magazine is probably still Wired magazine.<p>I have been a subscriber almost continuously from around 1994 or so.<p>Despite a history of excessive advertising and embarrassing flag waving about the glory of the internet economy Wired has consistently informed and entertained me with quality articles about the things that I enjoy:  internet, software, business, technology, politics, travel, etc.<p>It has also been a major innovator in terms of the visual style of magazines.  Their style was as new and different at its introduction as was MTV when it first appeared in the 80s.<p>The articles are largely targeted to 20 - 40 year old upper-middle-class, liberal technology industry oriented people, although I doubt there is anything in its content that conservatives or non-tech people would find offensive.<p>My issue goes straight into the toiletside magazine rack every month when it arrives.
      
