Works great, once you figure it out...
Like a lot of the other reviewers, part of the problem with this device is that it comes with absolutely no instructions. The device itself isn't hard to figure out, it's pretty straight forward... but there was one aspect of it that might have led to some of the bad reviews about this product:<br /><br />- It has both a iPod/iPhone connector and a 3.5mm audio connector. My first impression was to plug both in together; the Audio connector for, well, audio... and the iPod connector to charge it and enable the remote control use.<br /><br />When both connectors are connected, the audio quality is HORRIBLE... there is a loud high pitched hum, lots of static and the slightest movement of the device seemed to completely cut out the audio...<br /><br />Upset by this, I started to take my iPod Touch out of the cradle, and the first thing I disconnected was the 3.5mm audio connector and I paused for a moment as the audio continued to play and in PERFECT quality...<br /><br />So at this moment, I realized the iPod connector is an all-in-one connector... charges, enables the remote control use, and outputs audio to the cradle. Using only the iPod connector, the audio quality is superb and there is absolutely no static or humming at all.<br /><br />So if you have this product and you are experiencing a hum or static or just poor audio quality; try disconnecting the 3.5mm audio connector and just using the iPod connector.
      
