Well-priced spare or replacement battery
This battery works fine for my D70s. It has 2000 mAh compared to the Nikon 1500mAh. The case is brownish grey, not grey like the original and slips into the camera a tad less smooth than the original. <br /><br />Most important: you get what you see: cardboard box, tiny plastic bag, battery. No cover. Go to your attic and get the battery cover out of the original Nikon box where you left it when you originally assembled the rig. <br /><br />I don't know how much it would drive the price up but a battery cover would be a sensible add-on.
      
<!-- BOUNDARY -->
Completely Satisfied
Yes! Go ahead and purchase this battery! If you are reading this review and you are not sure if an off-brand battery is worth buying, let me be the one to assure you. This battery is pretty much the same as the one that came with my D90. Charges, performs and fits like the Nikon brand EN-EL3e battery. If you are stingy about the differences, the Nikon brand battery is a darker shade of grey than it's Opteka clone. Let me remind you that this difference does not effect the performance or quality of the battery itself.<br />Having this battery is nice since I'm doing a lot of video work with the D90. I have an external Nikon SB-400 flash unit so i dont have to worry about the camera battery's juice getting sucked up.
      
