Printing for pleasure...
My family bought this printer as our epson was slightly ancient. We were all delighted. The printer's 'fast draft' is quick and comes out reasnably clear, the 'normal' and 'fine' modes print pictures with amazing graphical quality. The scanner's resolution is great and will copy the smallest detail. The photocopying device is very simple to use and makes an identical copy of the page in either black or colour. Finally, this HP has a photo editing device that allows you to sharpen, brighten and remove 'red-eye' from any of the photo's on your har disc. This is a simple, user-friendly device that's cheap and reliable. I would advise whoever wants a great printing experince to try it out for themselves.
      
