high quality, affordable
I purchased a C4180 after my previous printer suddenly ceased all functioning - the day before a large research paper was due! I was impressed immediately by how easy setup for this printer was, as well as with all the options it provides controls for directly on the printer. The speed of printing was lightning-fast, and I was thrilled.<br />Unfortunately, I did run into problems - my photos printed in strange shades of purple (even when I set the print settings to black and white and to print in grayscale only!), the unit started to issue "paper jam" messages every time it was turned on, and shortly after it stopped printing altogether - the print cartridges were strangely stuck on one side of the printer, and no longer returned to their "home" position. I contacted HP's Customer Service via e-mail, described the problems in detail, and recieved suggestions promptly on how to possibly solve it. A few days after that, I recieved a follow-up e-mail, inquiring as to whether the strategies had worked. Although the suggestions unfortunately had not, because of the warranty HP provides on all of their products, they shipped me a different printer (same model) within about 5 days. This printer arrived with a prepaid shipping label so that I would not have to incur charges in mailing my own printer back to them as a return. I have been very satisfied with that C4180, and friends and family members are amazed at the quality with which photos print. Although yes, I did have some problems with my original C4180, I am giving this product five stars for the affordability, quality, and excellent customer service HP provides for their customers.
      
