Great Deal!
Great Treadmill. <br /><br />High quality components at a surprising price.<br /><br />Installation took me about an hour, and I had some trouble getting one bolt to fit, but perseverance prevailed and I made it through. Overall a very simple install and I received all of the parts necessary. They didn't include any spares, so hopefully you're not missing anything when it arrives.<br /><br />Heed their warnings about moving the treadmill around before the installation is completed. When you pick it up from the front, the bar can swing forward and hurt you or make you drop it if you're not careful. Take great care if you need to move this thing outside of the box before it's fully assembled.<br /><br />Applying the lubricant at the end was kind of a pain. I don't know why Merit couldn't do this at the factory, but at least it serves as a reminder to lube and shows you how to do it for the next time. (loosen the belt, shove your arm underneath, and squeeze)<br /><br />Pretty quiet for a treadmill. I'm 220lbs and put more strain on the motor than a lighter person, so it may even be quieter for you if you weigh less. It's nice to hear the TV while working out.<br /><br />Cup holders and the electronics are very nice as well. <br /><br />My HOA gym is a 5 minute walk away from my house, but I don't like going there because I don't like working out in public. This purchase has allowed me to work out in my basement for 30 minutes every night after work. Do whatever it takes to make working out convenient for you is my motto, since it is such an easy thing to skip.<br /><br />I've only had this thing for a short time and feel better already. Highly recommended! Overall a great purchase that I would make again in a heartbeat.
      
