Great Tent
Did a lot of research looking for a new tent this year. I finally just bit the bullet and went with this tent after being an avid Coleman person for years. I read several reviews about the Eureka brand I was impressed. I really liked the design of this tent and decided to give it a shot.<br />It has more than enough room for my boyfriend, my dog, and myself. The description doesn't make it clear, but all of the seams are factory sealed. The tent poles are color coded for easy set-up. We took the tent out about 5 times this year and I offer you the following from my experience.<br /><br />1. Read the directions. They include helpful tips that really make a difference. I don't normally like directions, but actually found these to be logical and helpful.<br />2. Put it up in the daylight the first time. Trust me you'll be thankful you did. After you know what you're doing it's a snap to do it in the dark.<br />3. The floor is a bit thin so purchase heavy tarp of tent pad to extend the life of your floor.<br /><br />My boyfriend and I are able to have this tent up and ready in 10 minutes flat - we both absolutely love it. He gave me a little grief at first when he hear how much it cost, but he agrees it has been worth every penny. It held up beautifully during a rain storm on our first trip and held it's ground solid during heavy winds on our last trip. I don't mind the fact that the flooring is lightweight because it makes it easier to fold, clean, and carry. I love the see through ceiling skylights, the secure rain fly and the incredible ventilation. We have absolutely no condensation inside our tent - even in humid Seattle weather. I was concerned that the high walls and mesh ceiling would cause it to not hold in the heat on chilly nights, but I was pleasantly surprised. I was not familiar with the Eureka brand prior to this purchase, but I can now say I will be a long term customer. My friends with tents from brand names like Kelty and North Face are equally impressed with the quality of this tent.
      
