Great trainer for a great price !!
I have a "mountain bike" (from Wal-Mart) which I've had for about 11 or 12 years, but it's in GREAT shape.  I haven't ridden it a whole lot, but bought this trainer in hopes of doing so. <br /><br />Being someone who isn't a "regular" biker, I didn't want to fork out tons of money on those trainers whose claim is to be the best for the best.  After reading MANY reviews, I chose this one.  It came assembled, ready to hold my bike.  After attempting to put my bike (with 26" wheels) on it, I remembered the one negative that a lot of people recognized -- the instructions defintely need improving.  But, after a little bit of time and thinking, I had my bike mounted and ready to go.<br /><br />I also read reviews about it being noisy.  I had a semi-slick tire put on my bike, and the noise doesn't really bother me -- I'm in a room in our garage watching tv or listening to the stereo -- definitely not a big deal - it creates no more noisy than a "wind bike", actually probably less.<br /><br />I definitely recommend it for anyone wishing to get more mileage out of their bike or just wishing to get some exercise without buying an extra piece of bulky exercise equipment.  This trainer can be folded and put out of the way quite easily.<br />
      
